  "texts": [
    "The concentration of available P is lower than the mean in most of the central and north portions of the study area but higher than the mean in the regions under the influence of the orogenic systems in the western, southern, and northern regions, characterized by elevations higher than 600 m (Fig. S6).",
    "The stock of organic P (Fig. 3) is 0.16 Pg P (22.5 % of the total P stock).",
    "The estimated mean concentration of organic P ranges from 19.6 to 247.18 mg kg -1, with mean values of 59.6 mg kg -1.",
    "The estimated stock of inorganic P (Fig. 4) is 0.08 Pg P (11.2 % of the estimated total P stock) with a mean concentration of 29.79 mg kg -1, ranging from 11.63 to 117.18 mg kg -1.",
    "The spatial patterns of organic and inorganic P concentrations follow the spatial pattern of the total P concentrations."
  ],
